modules.description: Provides functions to construct and chain I/O operations, including lifting values into the I/O monad, mapping over results, binding functions that return I/O, and signaling failures. Works with a monadic type `'a io` and HTTP request operations that simulate network calls. Used to simulate HTTP GET, POST, PUT, and DELETE requests in testing environments.

Provides functions to construct and send HTTP requests, parse JSON responses, and handle error cases during API interactions. Works with request configurations, JSON values, and HTTP client backends. Used to integrate OCaml applications with external web services, such as fetching user data from an API or submitting form information.

Provides operations to sequence I/O actions, transform results, and handle failures within a monadic context. Works with the `'a io` type to represent asynchronous or side-effecting computations. Executes HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE) with custom headers and processes responses as strings.
